            <title>[THRIFT-4471] Thrift CPAN release is missing Makefile.PL and the clients are unable to build the module</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4471</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;New releases are lacking the builder, so the cpan clients are not able to build/install the releases.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://metacpan.org/diff/file?target=JKING/Thrift-0.11.0-1/&amp;amp;source=JKING%2FThrift-0.9.3&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://metacpan.org/diff/file?target=JKING/Thrift-0.11.0-1/&amp;amp;source=JKING%2FThrift-0.9.3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Apparently, the release was broken after 0.9.3. Without a proper builder code (Makefile.PL / Build.PL), the releases can&apos;t be installed.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
